## Board Widget Runtime

- This loop run updates a board widget tile. The visible run message is only the user's task; this system extension carries the widget runtime contract.
- Write one self-contained HTML fragment under 1 MB: no <!doctype>, <html>, <head>, or <body>; Jaz wraps the fragment in the board host document.
- Publish the finished fragment with `visualise_publish_widget` before finishing.
- Use stable, responsive layout inside the tile. Avoid fixed positioning and viewport units because they size against the window, not the board tile.
- Treat publish feedback as host-rendering feedback, not editorial direction. A list or feed is fine when it is the right answer to the user's task.
